UNSCR#1284 1999...UN creates a new organisation of inspectors and threatens Sadaam to let the inspectors back in....He basically tells the UN to F**k off.
<br />
UNSCR#1441 2002...UN asks Sadaam for full disclosure of all WMD progeams and the distribution of left over stockpiles of weapons along with the reinstatement of all previous UN requests and a few more conditions including documentation satisfying the UN's demands. The UN gives Sadaam a deadline of 30 days or serious consequenses will result. 7 days before the deadline Sadaam gives the UN 12000 pages of documents which he tells the UN will answer all of its requests. After reviewing the 12000 pages the UN agress that 95% of the 12000 pages is documentation which Sadaam has previously given to the UN and the rest does not meet the terms of its fianl and last demand. UN deemed the document unacceptable. 
<br />

<br />
At this time the UN member countries agrue.  France, Germany, Russia and China want to give Sadaam yet another chance. Chance #18 even though they said that the last chance would be the last chance.
<br />

<br />
The UK, Spain, AUS, and 32 other countries follow the USA in the reasoning that after 12 years of defying the UN and sadaam having 17 previous chances to follow thru one the UN's resolutions and determine that Sadaams failure to comply on his last chance, that they will enforce the terms of the UNSCR#1441 threat of Serious consequesnes and demand that Sadaam comply or face war. These countries give Sadaam another deadline to submit to all of the UN's demands once and for all or leave power. If not they will attack. Sadaam says F**k off.
<br />

<br />
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------
<br />
Response to the USA Vetos  Vs. Sadaams violations of 17 UNSCRs...
<br />

<br />
As far as the USA using vetos in the UN...there is nothing wrong with the US using its veto power as that power was given to the USA by the UN to use. Doh....
<br />

<br />
My example was Sadaam defying UN resolutions. Not vetoing the UN.
<br />

<br />
Your comparison is like saying a 12ft skiff is better transportation then a BMW because the BMW can't cross a pond and the boat can.
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Give me an example where the USA has defied a UN resolution that was directed towards them which they failed to comply.</span> 
<br />

<br />
There aren't any...why? 
<br />

<br />
Because we have not violated any resolutions. Doh....
<br />

<br />
The USA uses its veto power because we can. We can veto anything we don't agree with.  
<br />

<br />
Ok let's give Sadaam veto power.....or Libya,  Doh......
<br />

<br />
Is that fair?
<br />

<br />
Maybe not, but its the rules that all the member countries agreed to. They gave us the veto power!
<br />

<br />
Your comparison of using vetos vs. defiance to resolutions is just plain stupid. I'm not saying your are stupid just the example does not make sense. 
<br />

<br />
I guess you dont agree with the USA's policy with Israel and need to get that into the debate...should probably start a different thread and I'll probably be on your side on that topic. 
<br />

<br />
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------
<br />

<br />
As far as the poll goes I am sure you are aware that there are over 23 million people that are Iraqi citizens, and they polled 4K? pftttt. Your quoted poll proves nothing. Did they ask the ones who are not confident about the USA succeeding why they aren't? 
<br />

<br />
Maybe its because of the Democrats like Dean who threaten to pull our soldiers out of Iraq and walk away from Iraq so Sadaam and other people who will aid terrorists or the terrorists themselves can come in, take over the country, and use its oil reserves to finance terrorism?
<br />

<br />
Maybe its because in 30 years of Sadaam rule no one has ever beaten Sadaam?
<br />

<br />
Maybe its because they are scared still of Sadaam?
<br />

<br />
Maybe its because they went to the citys across Iraq where there is the most intense fighting?
<br />

<br />
Do you think that because the UK conducted the poll that it is a more accurate poll than reality? I dont..just like in the USA there are UK citizens, media, pollsters just like you, who have an agenda.
<br />

<br />
Its been 7 months that we have been in Iraq..... why are you so impatient when the USA is still securing the country? We have captured or killed   80% of the Sadaam goverment officals (52 card deck) and we are working on the last few that remain in hiding. We also are eliminating the rest of the fanatics who have joined the fight.
<br />

<br />
WWII lasted for years, during that time there were days where we lost over 45, 000 troops in a single battle. Yes 45K of USA troops in one day DEAD!
<br />

<br />
Where has the pride/bravery of some of our citizens gone with regard to our responsibility to our children and future generations for the peace and security of the world. 
<br />

<br />
I guess Dean, Clinton and the rest of the peace loving pacifist Democrats
<br />
have set the example that you can just leave it up to someone else to make the sacrfice to secure peace in this world.
<br />

<br />
Dean goes to the draft with a doctors note excusing him from having to serve, Clinton dodged the draft.
<br />

<br />
Look at the brave who gave their lives for peace during WWII, you would be speaking German or Japanese right now if those brave patriots had not been there for us.
<br />

<br />
My dad liberated the Phillipenes in WWII and was in the Army. He landed on Manila and was in the 7th wave of attack. In case you did not know the first 4 waves all died. Well they drove the Japanese out. It was hell.
<br />

<br />
Does my dad hate the Japanese still. No he does not. 
<br />

<br />
In fact he married a Japanese woman, my mom who was terrified during the war and was scared stiff of the USA. She ended up falling in love with my dad. 
<br />

<br />
My father hated the Emperor and the Japanese goivernment officials who allied with Hitler and started the war. He never hated the Japanese people. My family understands that much good can come out of wars 1st hand.
<br />

<br />
As I said before wars are to be avoided. 
<br />

<br />
But not to the extent of of risking the security and freedom of the world.  Sadaam was a world threat... the pacifists would have brought that threat, horror, terrorism and dictatorship down upon us all.
<br />

<br />
Its gonna be a tough war...it may go on for years.. maybe decades ...it has to be fought. Will the USA make mistakes Yes...no country has ever fought a war without making mistakes. Can you demand that the USA be perfect and not make any? Sure you can.
<br />

<br />
I only hope we make as few mistakes as possible because mistakes cost lives.
<br />

<br />
Thank God Sadaam is gone. God is great!<br />_________________<br />Lady Dtresendes</span><span class="gensmall"><br /><br />Last edited by danille on Wed Dec 03, 2003 1:34 am; edited 2 times in total</span></td>
